WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.520
As an open-source data science developer, one of the most satisfying things I've worked on was

00:00:06.320 --> 00:00:13.280
in building Pandas, helping cross the cross-threshold between Python being usable and

00:00:13.280 --> 00:00:20.559
relevant in most business fields and not. So prior to that, people were interested in using Python,

00:00:20.559 --> 00:00:26.480
but they were struggling to jump in with both feet. And so Pandas helped them have the confidence

00:00:26.480 --> 00:00:30.480
that they could do their do their work in the programming language and start using it in a

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:37.119
in a serious way. And yeah, to go through that and to see the massive adoption of Python

00:00:37.119 --> 00:00:41.119
across the industry is definitely a lot of fun.

